#: ../../H/hack.rst:5
msgid "hack"
msgstr "hack"

#: ../../H/hack.rst:7
msgid "[very common]"
msgstr "[非常に一般的]"

#: ../../H/hack.rst:9
msgid "n\\. Originally, a quick job that produces what is needed, but not well."
msgstr "名詞 元来は、必要なものを生み出すが、出来は良くない手早い仕事。"

#: ../../H/hack.rst:12
msgid ""
"n\\. An incredibly good, and perhaps very time-consuming, piece of work that"
" produces exactly what is needed."
msgstr "名詞 信じられないほど良く、おそらく非常に時間のかかる、必要とされるものをまさに生み出す仕事。"

#: ../../H/hack.rst:15
msgid "vt\\. To bear emotionally or physically. \"I can't hack this heat!\""
msgstr "他動詞 感情的または肉体的に耐えること。「この暑さには耐えられない!」"

#: ../../H/hack.rst:19
msgid ""
"vt\\. To work on something (typically a program). In an immediate sense: "
"\"What are you doing?\" \"I'm hacking TECO.\" In a general (time-extended) "
"sense: \"What do you do around here?\" \"I hack TECO.\" More generally, \"I "
"hack foo\" is roughly equivalent to \"foo is my major interest (or "
"project)\". \"I hack solid-state physics.\" See :ref:`Hacking-X-for-Y`\\."
msgstr ""
"他動詞 "
"何か(通常はプログラム)に取り組むこと。直接的な意味で「何をしてるの?」「TECOをハックしてる」。一般的な(時間的に拡張された)意味で「ここらで何をしてるの?」「TECOをハックしてる」。より一般的に「I"
" hack foo」はおおよそ「fooが私の主な関心事(またはプロジェクト)だ」に等しい。「I hack solid-state "
"physics(固体物理をハックしてる)」。\\ :ref:`Hacking-X-for-Y`\\ を参照。"

#: ../../H/hack.rst:29
msgid "vt\\. To pull a prank on. See sense 2 and :ref:`hacker` (sense 5)."
msgstr "他動詞 いたずらを仕掛けること。語義2と\\ :ref:`hacker`\\ (語義5)を参照。"

#: ../../H/hack.rst:33
msgid ""
"vi\\. To interact with a computer in a playful and exploratory rather than "
"goal-directed way. \"Whatcha up to?\" \"Oh, just hacking.\""
msgstr "自動詞 目標指向ではなく、遊び心と探求心をもってコンピュータと対話すること。「何してるの?」「ああ、ただハックしてるだけ」。"

#: ../../H/hack.rst:38
msgid "n\\. Short for :ref:`hacker`\\."
msgstr "名詞 \\ :ref:`hacker`\\ の略。"

#: ../../H/hack.rst:42
msgid "See :ref:`nethack`\\."
msgstr "\\ :ref:`nethack`\\ を参照。"

#: ../../H/hack.rst:45
msgid ""
"[MIT] v. To explore the basements, roof ledges, and steam tunnels of a "
"large, institutional building, to the dismay of Physical Plant workers and "
"(since this is usually performed at educational institutions) the Campus "
"Police. This activity has been found to be eerily similar to playing "
"adventure games such as Dungeons and Dragons and :ref:`Zork`\\. See also "
":ref:`vadding`\\."
msgstr ""
"[MIT]動詞 "
"大きな施設建物の地下室、屋根の縁、蒸気トンネルを探検すること。設備管理作業員や(これは通常教育機関で行われるので)キャンパス警察を狼狽させながら。この活動は、Dungeons"
" and Dragonsや\\ :ref:`Zork`\\ のようなアドベンチャーゲームをプレイするのと不気味なほど似ていることが判明している。\\ "
":ref:`vadding`\\ も参照。"

#: ../../H/hack.rst:49
msgid ""
"Constructions on this term abound. They include happy hacking (a farewell), "
"how's hacking? (a friendly greeting among hackers) and hack, hack (a fairly "
"content-free but friendly comment, often used as a temporary farewell). For "
"more on this totipotent term see * The Meaning of Hack*\\. See also "
":ref:`neat-hack`\\, :ref:`real-hack`\\."
msgstr ""
"この用語の上に作られた言い回しは数多い。それらにはhappy hacking(別れの挨拶)、how's "
"hacking?(ハッカー間の親しげな挨拶)、hack, "
"hack(かなり内容のない、だが親しげなコメント。一時的な別れの挨拶としてよく使われる)が含まれる。この万能の用語についてさらに知るには\\ *The "
"Meaning of Hack*\\ を参照。\\ :ref:`neat-hack`\\ 、\\ :ref:`real-hack`\\ も参照。"
